Google Playstore Data Analysis Dashboard (Power BI Project)
ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project presents an in-depth data analysis of the Google Play Store to understand how different factors â€” such as app category, price type, user ratings, and reviews â€” influence app performance. The Power BI dashboard highlights key patterns in app ratings, user engagement, and free vs paid app distribution, providing valuable insights into market behavior and opportunities for app developers.

ğŸ¯ Objective

To analyze and visualize app performance data from the Google Playstore dataset using Power BI, identifying trends in:

App ratings across categories

Free vs. paid app performance

Number of reviews and user engagement over time

Relationship between genres and user satisfaction

ğŸ—‚ï¸ Dataset Source

Source: Kaggle (Google Play Store Dataset)

Data Type: Public dataset containing app details such as category, genre, price, rating, and number of reviews

Size: ~10,000 app records

Format: CSV file

ğŸ§® Data Preparation

Initial data cleaning and transformation were performed in Microsoft Excel, followed by modeling and visualization in Power BI.

Key Data Cleaning Steps (Excel):

Removed duplicates and invalid entries

Handled missing ratings and review counts

Standardized category and genre names

Filtered out irrelevant or incomplete records

Power BI Processing:

Imported cleaned dataset

Created DAX measures for:

Total Apps

Total Free Apps & Paid Apps

Average Rating

Average Reviews per App

Churn and Rating Distributions

Designed interactive visuals with slicers and filters by category, genre, and app type.

ğŸ“Š Dashboard Metrics and KPIs

The dashboard provides insights through the following visuals:

Metric	Description
Total Apps	Total number of apps analyzed (~7,000)
Total Free vs. Paid Apps	Distribution of free (6,000+) vs paid (541) apps
Average Rating	Overall user rating across apps (~4.2)
Average Reviews per App	~145K average reviews
Top 10 Categories by Average Rating	Personalization, Games, Sports, Family, and Medical lead with ratings above 4.2
Top 10 Genres by Total Ratings	Tools, Entertainment, and Education dominate
Free vs. Paid App Distribution by Genre	Majority of apps across all genres are free
Total Reviews by Year Updated	Significant rise in review counts post-2016, peaking in 2018
ğŸ’¡ Key Insights

Based on the analysis and dashboard visuals:

Free apps dominate the Play Store, representing nearly 92% of total apps, while paid apps make up a small fraction (~8%).

Average user rating stands at 4.2, indicating overall strong user satisfaction.

Personalization and Game apps receive the highest average ratings (4.3â€“4.2), reflecting user preference for entertainment and customization features.

Tools, Entertainment, and Education genres have the highest total number of ratings, showing large active user bases.

User reviews increased sharply between 2016 and 2018, suggesting the surge of smartphone app adoption during this period.

Paid apps tend to have slightly higher average ratings, indicating better perceived quality, though fewer in number.

Most app categories maintain consistent performance trends, implying competitive parity within major genres.

